For the reducer, we will keep a running list of the top 3 records. We don't need the complex current_key logic because the key is always "all".

Python
import sys

top_records = [] # List to hold tuples of (score, record_string)

for line in sys.stdin:
    dummy_key, record = line.strip().split('\t', 1)
    
    # Extract the score from the record (Assuming format "Name,Score")
    score = int(record.split(',')[1])
    
    # Add to our list
    top_records.append((score, record))
    
    # Sort the list in descending order based on the score (x[0])
    top_records.sort(reverse=True, key=lambda x: x[0])
    
    # Keep only the top 3
    top_records = top_records[:3]

# Print the final top 3 records
for score, record in top_records:
    print(record)
